ClMRD9A==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing XML features**\\n\\nI need to add new tests but wonder if the existing ones still run. I'll opt for robust testing, and maybe the existing tests now pass, but we haven't run them. I should keep the existing tests unchanged while considering a feature like `XmlDefault`. I need to clarify behavior and perhaps use `XML.Companion` for simpler, high coverage. There are details like root QName override and XML declaration modes, and I might include two tests to ensure coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining XML serialization**\\n\\nI’m looking at how encoding would use a structure like `<m:manifest xmlns:m=... id=...><m:title>...`, and decoding it with the right method should return a value. The `QName` prefix is standard in javax, so that's good. I need to test XML declaration modes, like Minimal or Charset, to ensure they produce the correct XML version output.\\n\\nI’m also considering features like property order with `@XmlBefore/@XmlAfter`. I could create a data class `Ordered` for testing. But I wonder if it's outputting as attributes by default, which might require `XmlElement(true)` for elements. I’ll need to be careful about ordering as well!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_s1naB88Rnx9WdcgN4JjvEDDU|fc_0066cfd37b3aaa770169f8b10219948193ad187b7612e69ae7", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.github.pdvrieze.xmlutil/serialization-jvm/0.91.3/src/test/kotlin/io_github_pdvrieze_xmlutil/serialization_jvm/RootNameAndOrderingTest.kt", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_github_pdvrieze_xmlutil.serialization_jvm\n\nimport kotlinx.serialization.Serializable\nimport nl.adaptivity.xmlutil.XmlDeclMode\nimport nl.adaptivity.xmlutil.serialization.XML\nimport nl.adaptivity.xmlutil.serialization.XmlAfter\nimport nl.adaptivity.xmlutil.serialization.XmlBefore\nimport nl.adaptivity.xmlutil.serialization.XmlElement\nimport nl.adaptivity.xmlutil.serialization.XmlSerialName\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\nimport javax.xml.namespace.QName\n\npublic class RootNameAndOrderingTest {\n    @Test\n    fun explicitRootQNameOverridesDescriptorNameAndRoundTrips(): Unit {\n        val xml = XML {\n            xmlDeclMode = XmlDeclMode.None\n            repairNamespaces = true\n        }\n        val rootName = QName(ROOT_NAMESPACE, \"manifest\", \"m\")\n        val manifest = RootNamedManifest(\n            id = \"manifest-42\",\n            title = \"Native image metadata\",\n            owner = \"xmlutil\",\n        )\n\n        val encoded: String = xml.encodeToString(RootNamedManifest.serializer(), manifest, rootName)\n\n        assertThat(encoded)\n            .contains(\"<m:manifest\")\n            .contains(\"xmlns:m=\\\"$ROOT_NAMESPACE\\\"\")\n            .contains(\"id=\\\"manifest-42\\\"\")\n            .contains(\"Native image metadata\")\n        assertThat(xml.xmlDescriptor(RootNamedManifest.serializer(), rootName).tagName).isEqualTo(rootName)\n        assertThat(xml.decodeFromString(RootNamedManifest.serializer(), encoded, rootName)).isEqualTo(manifest)\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun beforeAndAfterAnnotationsReorderElementChildrenDuringEncoding(): Unit {\n        val xml = XML { xmlDeclMode = XmlDeclMode.None }\n        val event = OrderedLifecycleEvent(\n            last = \"archive\",\n            middle = \"publish\",\n            first = \"build\",\n        )\n\n        val encoded: String = xml.encodeToString(OrderedLifecycleEvent.serializer(), event)\n\n        val firstIndex: Int = encoded.indexOf(\"<first>build</first>\")\n        val middleIndex: Int = encoded.indexOf(\"<middle>publish</middle>\")\n        val lastIndex: Int = encoded.indexOf(\"<last>archive</last>\")\n        assertThat(firstIndex).isGreaterThanOrEqualTo(0)\n        assertThat(middleIndex).isGreaterThan(firstIndex)\n        assertThat(lastIndex).isGreaterThan(middleIndex)\n        assertThat(xml.decodeFromString(OrderedLifecycleEvent.serializer(), encoded)).isEqualTo(event)\n    }\n\n    private companion object {\n        private const val ROOT_NAMESPACE: String = \"urn:test:explicit-root\"\n    }\n}\n\n@Serializable\n@XmlSerialName(\"payload\")\nprivate data class RootNamedManifest(\n    @XmlElement(false)\n    val id: String,\n    @XmlElement(true)\n    val title: String,\n    @XmlElement(true)\n    val owner: String,\n)\n\n@Serializable\n@XmlSerialName(\"lifecycle\")\nprivate data class OrderedLifecycleEvent(\n    @XmlElement(true)\n    @XmlAfter(\"middle\")\n    val last: String,\n    @XmlElement(true)\n    val middle: String,\n    @XmlElement(true)\n    @XmlBefore(\"middle\")\n    val first: String,\n)\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3518, "output": 2001, "cacheRead": 81920, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 87439, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777905905590, "responseId": "resp_0066cfd37b3aaa770169f8b0f267fc81938d08b73b6373e47a"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_s1naB88Rnx9WdcgN4JjvEDDU|fc_0066cfd37b3aaa770169f8b10219948193ad187b7612e69ae7", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 3197 bytes to tests/src/io.github.pdvrieze.xmlutil/serialization-jvm/0.91.3/src/test/kotlin/io_github_pdvrieze_xmlutil/serialization_jvm/RootNameAndOrderingTest.kt"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777905927188}]}
